This article is a transcript of a press gaggle by Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton aboard Air Force One. Burton discusses various topics including the President's message for the press, the reappointment of Ben Bernanke, reports on Anwar al-Awlaki, the President's involvement in the Senate vote, the President's plans to sell health care reform to the public, CEO compensation at Fannie and Freddie, aid to states with budget difficulties, the President's reading list and activities in Hawaii, the First Family's Christmas plans, and the security of Rahm Emanuel's job. Burton declines to comment on specific reports and details about the President's gifts and Christmas plans.